<h1>RSC FOUC Demo — issue #3211</h1>
<p>
  Reproduces the bug: CSS imported behind a <code>&apos;use client&apos;</code> boundary
  inside a true RSC tree is not hoisted into <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> by React on Rails Pro,
  so it only loads as a side-effect of the client JS chunk evaluating, producing FOUC.
</p>

<%= stream_react_component("RSCFOUCDemo",
    props: { artificialDelay: (params[:artificial_delay].presence || 0).to_i },
    prerender: true,
    trace: true,
    id: "rsc-fouc-demo-ssr") %>
